{"title_page": "Outlaws of Sonora", "text_new": "{{short description|1938 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Outlaws of Sonora\n| caption        = Film poster\n| image\t         = Outlaws of Sonora FilmPoster.jpeg\n| director       = [[George Sherman]]\n| producer       = [[William Berke]]\n| writer         = [[William Colt MacDonald]]<br>[[Betty Burbridge]]<br>[[Edmond Kelso]]\n| starring       = [[Robert Livingston (actor)|Robert Livingston]]<br>[[Ray Corrigan]]<br>[[Max Terhune]]\n| music          = [[Alberto Colombo (composer)|Alberto Colombo]]\n| cinematography = William Nobles\n| editing        = Tony Martinelli\n| distributor    = [[Republic Pictures]]\n| released       = {{film date|1938|4|14}}\n| runtime        = 55 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n}}\n\n'''''Outlaws of Sonora''''' is a 1938 American [[Western (genre)|Western]] \"[[The Three Mesquiteers|Three Mesquiteers]]\" [[B-movie]]<ref name=\"b-westerns\">{{cite web |url=http://www.b-westerns.com/trio3m7.htm |title=The Three Mesquiteers Trio Westerns of Republic Pictures |accessdate=August 29, 2011|work=b-westerns.com}}</ref> directed by [[George Sherman]].\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Robert Livingston (actor)|Robert Livingston]] as Stony Brooke\n* [[Ray Corrigan]] as Tucson Smith\n* [[Max Terhune]] as Lullaby Joslin\n* [[Jack Mulhall]] as Dr. George Martin\n* [[Otis Harlan]] as Pool player\n* Jean Joyce as Miss McCoy, Secretary\n* Sterlita Peluffo as Rosita (as Stelita Peluffo)\n* [[Tom London]] as Sheriff Trask\n* Gloria Rich as Stoney's friend\n* Edwin Mordant as Banker Pierce\n* Ralph Peters as Henchman Gabby\n* [[George Chesebro]] as Henchman Slim\n* Frank LaRue as Coroner\n* [[Jack Ingram (actor)|Jack Ingram]] as Henchman Nick\n* [[Merrill McCormick]] as Henchman Pete\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb title|id=0030538|title=Outlaws of Sonora}}\n\n{{George Sherman}}\n{{The Three Mesquiteers}}\n\n{